TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Fit between Technology and Structure as a Predictor of Performance in Nursing Subunits
AU  - Alexander, Judith W.
AU  - Randolph, W. Alan
Y1  - 1985/12/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256240
DO  - 10.5465/256240
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 844
EP  - 859
VL  - 28
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Regression analyses of field study data from 27 nursing subunits supported the hypothesis that a simple measure of fit between technology and structure is a better predictor of quality of care than either technology or structure alone, or the two together. The results of this study were thus consistent with the growing body of congruency literature, and they suggest that a simple measure of structure may be quite useful in such research.
AB  - Regression analyses of field study data from 27 nursing subunits supported the hypothesis that a simple measure of fit between technology and structure is a better predictor of quality of care than either technology or structure alone, or the two together. The results of this study were thus consistent with the growing body of congruency literature, and they suggest that a simple measure of structure may be quite useful in such research.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256240
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256240
