T1  - Product-Market Diversification and Market Power
AU  - Montgomery, Cynthia A.
Y1  - 1985/12/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256237
DO  - 10.5465/256237
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 789
EP  - 798
VL  - 28
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examines relationships among diversification, market structure, and firm performance. Theory and empirical data are offered that argue that highly diversified firms have lower market power in their respective markets than do less diversified firms. This view is contrasted with the traditional market power theory that emphasizes the general rather than the specific market power of diversified firms.
AB  - This study examines relationships among diversification, market structure, and firm performance. Theory and empirical data are offered that argue that highly diversified firms have lower market power in their respective markets than do less diversified firms. This view is contrasted with the traditional market power theory that emphasizes the general rather than the specific market power of diversified firms.
