T1  - Mode of Corporate Diversification and Economic Performance
AU  - Lamont, Bruce T.
AU  - Anderson, Carl R.
Y1  - 1985/12/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256245
DO  - 10.5465/256245
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 926
EP  - 934
VL  - 28
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - In this article the authors discuss research they conducted on the diversification strategies used by multibusiness corporations. Two of the strategies that they identify include internal diversification that relies on the development of products or services and external diversification that relies on the acquisition of other firms. They hypothesized that multibusiness firms diversify into new business by using one of these two methods while avoiding mixing of the two strategies and that corporations that do mix strategies experience lower economic returns than corporations that avoid this method.
AB  - In this article the authors discuss research they conducted on the diversification strategies used by multibusiness corporations. Two of the strategies that they identify include internal diversification that relies on the development of products or services and external diversification that relies on the acquisition of other firms. They hypothesized that multibusiness firms diversify into new business by using one of these two methods while avoiding mixing of the two strategies and that corporations that do mix strategies experience lower economic returns than corporations that avoid this method.
